1
00:01:37,300 --> 00:01:42,080
[The Storm of Roses]

2
00:01:42,330 --> 00:01:44,789
[Episode 16]

3
00:01:51,830 --> 00:01:53,120
You're pretty good at this?

4
00:01:54,509 --> 00:01:55,390
If so, come on.

5
00:01:57,710 --> 00:01:58,420
Okay.

6
00:02:21,680 --> 00:02:22,829
Awesome!

7
00:02:22,870 --> 00:02:23,790
Di,

8
00:02:23,820 --> 00:02:25,970
if you tie with him, I'll treat the whole team to barbecue.

9
00:02:26,300 --> 00:02:27,530
Sounds good!

10
00:03:06,410 --> 00:03:06,960
Nice move!

11
00:03:07,150 --> 00:03:07,830
Nice.

12
00:03:49,110 --> 00:03:50,310
Let's take a five-second break then.

13
00:03:50,390 --> 00:03:51,150
You look tired.

14
00:03:57,710 --> 00:03:58,710
Wasn't that a foul?

15
00:03:58,890 --> 00:04:00,430
That was a shameless move.

16
00:04:00,590 --> 00:04:02,440
Didn't you say we'd take a five-second break?

17
00:04:02,590 --> 00:04:04,590
If you trust your enemy on the battlefield,

18
00:04:05,390 --> 00:04:06,850
it's like committing suicide.

19
00:04:21,079 --> 00:04:22,040
They're not going to fight, are they?

20
00:04:30,230 --> 00:04:30,970
What?

21
00:04:34,140 --> 00:04:35,030
Nothing.

22
00:04:35,620 --> 00:04:36,500
How about eating some kebabs?

23
00:04:45,000 --> 00:04:49,170
[Freshwater Fish]

24
00:04:49,200 --> 00:04:51,510
[Tu's Watch Repair Shop]

25
00:04:51,659 --> 00:05:00,200
[Shidazi Snacks]

26
00:05:00,030 --> 00:05:01,550
It's delicious. So spicy.

27
00:05:01,630 --> 00:05:02,680
I think it's not bad.

28
00:05:02,750 --> 00:05:03,700
Delicious.

29
00:05:06,670 --> 00:05:07,670
Awesome guy.

30
00:05:07,840 --> 00:05:08,410
Awesome guy!

31
00:05:09,870 --> 00:05:10,650
Eat.

32
00:05:11,540 --> 00:05:13,240
Have some more.

33
00:05:13,600 --> 00:05:14,780
Try this.

34
00:05:16,900 --> 00:05:18,270
You picked a great place.

35
00:05:18,340 --> 00:05:18,910
It's good, isn't it?

36
00:05:18,990 --> 00:05:19,810
I come here often.

37
00:05:19,840 --> 00:05:21,670
Let's make a toast to Ma.

38
00:05:21,670 --> 00:05:22,990
Come on. We should.

39
00:05:22,990 --> 00:05:24,790
-Thank you, Ma.
-Thank you, Ma.

40
00:05:24,790 --> 00:05:26,340
Thanks for the meal, Ma.

41
00:05:30,600 --> 00:05:31,470
Take it easy, everyone.

42
00:05:31,470 --> 00:05:32,070
Drink slowly.

43
00:05:32,230 --> 00:05:32,870
Today,

44
00:05:32,870 --> 00:05:33,790
Ma is generous enough

45
00:05:33,790 --> 00:05:35,830
to treat us to this hearty meal.

46
00:05:35,950 --> 00:05:36,950
So this is... is...

47
00:05:37,070 --> 00:05:38,200
fate, right?

48
00:05:38,590 --> 00:05:40,040
Able... Able men are always busy.

49
00:05:40,230 --> 00:05:41,630
Eat as much as you can.

50
00:05:41,630 --> 00:05:42,510
If it's not enough, we'll order more.

51
00:05:42,510 --> 00:05:43,310
Absolutely.

52
00:05:43,310 --> 00:05:44,030
What did you say?

53
00:05:44,030 --> 00:05:45,909
Shouldn't you say that behind my back?

54
00:05:45,909 --> 00:05:47,110
I'm still here.

55
00:05:47,470 --> 00:05:48,990
I'll foot the bill today.

56
00:05:48,990 --> 00:05:49,670
Go ahead and eat.

57
00:05:49,670 --> 00:05:51,070
Stop talking about me, alright?

58
00:05:51,190 --> 00:05:52,390
Then how about some more alcohol?

59
00:05:52,390 --> 00:05:53,270
We've finished it all.

60
00:05:53,350 --> 00:05:55,110
The alcohol we just ordered is too little.

61
00:05:55,110 --> 00:05:55,870
Look, it's empty.

62
00:05:55,870 --> 00:05:57,670
You already had a drink with everyone here, right?

63
00:05:57,670 --> 00:05:58,510
So what?

64
00:05:58,510 --> 00:05:59,310
-What?
-You don't want us to drink anymore?

65
00:05:59,310 --> 00:06:01,050
You and Di drank the most.

66
00:06:01,190 --> 00:06:02,270
Well, listen,

67
00:06:02,390 --> 00:06:03,890
young ladies really should

68
00:06:04,000 --> 00:06:05,270
drink less when they're outside.

69
00:06:05,270 --> 00:06:06,320
I'm saying it for your own good.

70
00:06:06,350 --> 00:06:07,150
-You...
-What?

71
00:06:08,310 --> 00:06:09,750
I admire Ma the most.

72
00:06:09,750 --> 00:06:11,270
He managed to explain the concept of stinginess in such an elegant way.

73
00:06:11,270 --> 00:06:11,790
Yeah.

74
00:06:11,790 --> 00:06:12,630
Only Ma can do that.

75
00:06:12,630 --> 00:06:13,550
What do you mean by stinginess?

76
00:06:13,550 --> 00:06:14,640
That's right.

77
00:06:15,030 --> 00:06:15,730
How about this?

78
00:06:16,340 --> 00:06:17,650
The alcohol is on me.

79
00:06:17,950 --> 00:06:18,430
Okay?

80
00:06:18,430 --> 00:06:19,650
How can we let you treat us?

81
00:06:19,690 --> 00:06:20,870
Are you from a rich family or something?

82
00:06:20,950 --> 00:06:21,550
No, I'm not.

83
00:06:21,550 --> 00:06:22,830
You think I'd have the heart to drink the alcohol you buy?

84
00:06:22,830 --> 00:06:23,510
You wouldn't.

85
00:06:23,510 --> 00:06:25,350
But I don't feel bad about drinking the alcohol Ma buys.

86
00:06:26,470 --> 00:06:27,390
None of us feel bad about it.

87
00:06:27,390 --> 00:06:28,500
None of you feel bad?

88
00:06:28,710 --> 00:06:30,710
We can't always take advantage of Ma, right?

89
00:06:30,710 --> 00:06:31,230
Yeah.

90
00:06:31,230 --> 00:06:32,150
-Di is right.
-How about this?

91
00:06:32,190 --> 00:06:33,470
I'll ask someone to go with me to get more alcohol.

92
00:06:33,520 --> 00:06:34,280
Can you do it?

93
00:06:40,370 --> 00:06:41,110
I'll go.

94
00:06:41,110 --> 00:06:42,350
Girls don't know much about alcohol, right?

95
00:06:46,990 --> 00:06:47,510
Eat.

96
00:06:47,700 --> 00:06:48,190
Let's go.

97
00:06:48,190 --> 00:06:48,750
The dishes are getting cold.

98
00:06:48,750 --> 00:06:49,340
Hurry up and eat.

99
00:06:49,590 --> 00:06:50,350
Just eat.

100
00:06:50,350 --> 00:06:51,180
Hurry up and eat.

101
00:06:51,180 --> 00:06:52,110
Have some more.

102
00:06:53,440 --> 00:06:54,350
You're not observant at all.

103
00:06:54,350 --> 00:06:55,390
Just eat more.

104
00:06:55,390 --> 00:06:56,190
You wanted to go?

105
00:06:56,190 --> 00:06:56,909
You're nosy.

106
00:06:56,909 --> 00:06:57,830
Nothing is going on.

107
00:06:58,230 --> 00:06:59,590
How come you are so dense?

108
00:07:05,460 --> 00:07:07,000
They're a bit noisy.

109
00:07:07,510 --> 00:07:08,990
Are you not used to it?

110
00:07:09,010 --> 00:07:09,730
It's alright.

111
00:07:12,070 --> 00:07:14,780
You're quite good at fencing.

112
00:07:15,080 --> 00:07:16,030
How long have you learned it?

113
00:07:17,410 --> 00:07:18,840
I just started early.

114
00:07:18,870 --> 00:07:19,630
Since middle school.

115
00:07:22,080 --> 00:07:23,940
Why don't you join our fencing team?

116
00:07:26,140 --> 00:07:27,310
It depends on my schedule.

117
00:07:27,860 --> 00:07:28,980
If there is a chance,

118
00:07:29,000 --> 00:07:29,530
I'll think about it.

119
00:07:30,430 --> 00:07:32,120
Are you very busy with work?

120
00:07:34,560 --> 00:07:35,120
Yes.

121
00:07:38,140 --> 00:07:38,930
Let me ask you.

122
00:07:39,430 --> 00:07:41,340
You just said

123
00:07:42,110 --> 00:07:44,260
taking a five-second break.

124
00:07:44,370 --> 00:07:46,050
Did you just want to teach me a lesson?

125
00:07:47,480 --> 00:07:49,540
It's not that difficult to deal with you.

126
00:07:49,850 --> 00:07:51,670
That's insulting.

127
00:07:51,670 --> 00:07:52,310
I didn't mean that.

128
00:07:52,310 --> 00:07:53,720
I just want you to know

129
00:07:54,500 --> 00:07:56,040
the person standing opposite you

130
00:07:56,350 --> 00:07:57,310
is your enemy.

131
00:07:57,310 --> 00:07:58,440
From that moment on,

132
00:07:58,470 --> 00:08:00,280
you need to know everything about him.

133
00:08:00,670 --> 00:08:03,220
You need to pay attention to his real intention.

134
00:08:04,190 --> 00:08:06,610
So never trust your enemy.

135
00:08:07,860 --> 00:08:08,490
Also,

136
00:08:09,380 --> 00:08:11,240
I believe the best defense is a good offense.

137
00:08:11,270 --> 00:08:11,910
It's true in fencing,

138
00:08:11,910 --> 00:08:13,130
and in life as well.

139
00:08:18,100 --> 00:08:19,580
Do you always talk

140
00:08:19,580 --> 00:08:21,510
so seriously about everything?

141
00:08:21,820 --> 00:08:22,750
Doesn't it tire you out?

142
00:08:24,930 --> 00:08:26,750
Actually, we've met a few times before.

143
00:08:27,040 --> 00:08:27,980
You don't remember?

144
00:08:28,150 --> 00:08:29,550
In the taxi.

145
00:08:29,590 --> 00:08:30,910
We shared a taxi ride.

146
00:08:30,910 --> 00:08:31,510
I haven't forgotten.

147
00:08:31,510 --> 00:08:32,150
I remember.

148
00:08:33,039 --> 00:08:33,659
Thank you.

149
00:08:35,390 --> 00:08:36,100
How about this?

150
00:08:36,120 --> 00:08:37,669
Let's reintroduce ourselves to each other.

151
00:08:38,030 --> 00:08:38,710
Come on.

152
00:08:40,190 --> 00:08:41,380
I'm Jiang Yidi.

153
00:08:41,440 --> 00:08:43,850
You can call me Yidi or Jiang.

154
00:08:46,940 --> 00:08:47,630
Eason.

155
00:08:47,710 --> 00:08:48,460
Eason?

156
00:08:49,140 --> 00:08:50,830
You like Eason Chan?

157
00:08:52,660 --> 00:08:53,410
No.

158
00:08:55,870 --> 00:08:56,550
Eason.

159
00:09:01,980 --> 00:09:02,740
Eason,

160
00:09:02,830 --> 00:09:03,640
let me ask you.

161
00:09:04,070 --> 00:09:05,680
Which industry do you work in?

162
00:09:06,230 --> 00:09:07,500
I'm dressing like this.

163
00:09:07,520 --> 00:09:08,210
Finance.

164
00:09:08,480 --> 00:09:09,080
Finance?

165
00:09:09,080 --> 00:09:09,470
Yes.

166
00:09:10,190 --> 00:09:11,330
So, are you in

167
00:09:11,590 --> 00:09:13,230
stocks, funds,

168
00:09:13,270 --> 00:09:15,990
insurance, or investment banking?

169
00:09:15,990 --> 00:09:17,000
Well, do you always ask

170
00:09:17,000 --> 00:09:18,020
so many questions?

171
00:09:18,020 --> 00:09:20,030
If... If we just met...

172
00:09:20,030 --> 00:09:21,990
Is... Is this a habit of yours?

173
00:09:24,930 --> 00:09:25,830
So you know

174
00:09:25,830 --> 00:09:27,470
being overly inquisitive can make others feel uncomfortable,

175
00:09:27,490 --> 00:09:28,090
Mr. Yu.

176
00:09:46,270 --> 00:09:47,680
When did you find it out?

177
00:09:50,510 --> 00:09:51,510
Not long ago.

178
00:10:00,120 --> 00:10:01,000
Mike.

179
00:10:01,240 --> 00:10:02,940
Does our company have a new member?

180
00:10:03,920 --> 00:10:05,230
Just the new boss?

181
00:10:07,690 --> 00:10:08,800
What's his name?

182
00:10:09,540 --> 00:10:11,050
Which Yu and which Shi?

183
00:10:11,250 --> 00:10:13,090
[Yu Shi]

184
00:10:13,230 --> 00:10:14,140
[Honors]

185
00:10:18,850 --> 00:10:20,070
You're quite observant.

186
00:10:22,420 --> 00:10:23,690
You have a good memory too.

187
00:10:24,390 --> 00:10:25,730
And you're quite composed.

188
00:10:27,340 --> 00:10:27,970
Very good.

189
00:10:28,230 --> 00:10:29,990
Boss, thank you for praising me.

190
00:10:30,010 --> 00:10:30,740
Boss?

191
00:10:31,080 --> 00:10:32,310
I took office over a week ago.

192
00:10:32,310 --> 00:10:34,220
You're my most difficult employee to arrange a meeting with.

193
00:10:35,470 --> 00:10:36,510
Why did you resign?

194
00:10:37,180 --> 00:10:37,950
You've got a new job?

195
00:10:37,950 --> 00:10:38,710
Which company?

196
00:10:42,360 --> 00:10:43,400
Don't you know?

197
00:10:44,960 --> 00:10:47,360
I got suspended by the company.

198
00:10:51,930 --> 00:10:53,180
Why?

199
00:10:55,220 --> 00:10:56,700
Due to improper reimbursement, I guess.

200
00:10:58,410 --> 00:10:59,520
Did you violate the rules?

201
00:11:00,170 --> 00:11:01,590
If I say I didn't,

202
00:11:01,980 --> 00:11:02,900
would you believe me?

203
00:11:04,250 --> 00:11:05,200
I believe...

204
00:11:05,450 --> 00:11:06,170
the facts.

205
00:11:09,540 --> 00:11:10,500
You...

206
00:11:11,000 --> 00:11:13,330
Can't you... Can't you just say you believe me?

207
00:11:13,510 --> 00:11:14,280
Is it that difficult?

208
00:11:14,320 --> 00:11:14,880
It's not difficult.

209
00:11:15,520 --> 00:11:16,510
But I won't.

210
00:11:17,510 --> 00:11:19,810
Because when I judge situations and people,

211
00:11:19,830 --> 00:11:21,560
the last thing I rely on is subjectivity.

212
00:11:23,780 --> 00:11:25,540
Okay, Eason.

213
00:11:27,180 --> 00:11:28,080
That's a fair point.

214
00:11:28,100 --> 00:11:32,630
No one would believe someone else for no reason.

215
00:11:32,870 --> 00:11:33,410
Right?

216
00:11:39,540 --> 00:11:40,300
Eason.

217
00:11:43,500 --> 00:11:44,490
I'll pay.

218
00:11:44,530 --> 00:11:47,070
During your suspension, I suggest you reduce expenses and increase income.

219
00:11:47,310 --> 00:11:48,470
Don't look down on me.

220
00:11:48,490 --> 00:11:50,190
I can still afford alcohol.

221
00:11:50,590 --> 00:11:51,300
Waitress.

222
00:11:51,740 --> 00:11:53,950
What's the most expensive red wine you have here?

223
00:11:54,090 --> 00:11:56,370
The most expensive one is this one here. 350 yuan per bottle.

224
00:11:57,190 --> 00:11:58,620
We'll... have two bottles.

225
00:11:59,030 --> 00:11:59,670
Okay.

226
00:11:59,940 --> 00:12:01,040
He's paying.

227
00:12:01,350 --> 00:12:02,070
Okay.

228
00:12:02,230 --> 00:12:03,110
I'll buy beer.

229
00:12:03,200 --> 00:12:04,160
Thank you, Boss.

230
00:12:15,230 --> 00:12:15,990
Is it heavy,

231
00:12:16,590 --> 00:12:17,110
Boss?

232
00:12:19,510 --> 00:12:20,570
Do you need my help?

233
00:12:21,990 --> 00:12:22,800
No need.

234
00:12:22,830 --> 00:12:23,790
I'm fine.

235
00:12:35,150 --> 00:12:36,750
What do you plan to do next?

236
00:12:37,560 --> 00:12:38,400
I'll...

237
00:12:40,170 --> 00:12:41,270
drink alcohol,

238
00:12:41,270 --> 00:12:42,270
eat meat,

239
00:12:42,310 --> 00:12:42,830
and have fun.

240
00:12:50,730 --> 00:12:53,050
But if you want the truth â€”

241
00:12:57,150 --> 00:12:58,360
I don't want to leave.

242
00:12:59,870 --> 00:13:01,970
It's not because I can't find another job.

243
00:13:02,280 --> 00:13:03,960
I just can't accept it.

244
00:13:05,710 --> 00:13:06,590
There's something

245
00:13:06,590 --> 00:13:07,430
I want to tell you.

246
00:13:09,480 --> 00:13:11,780
The two bottles of wine you bought today

247
00:13:12,370 --> 00:13:13,050
are worth it.

248
00:13:15,830 --> 00:13:16,630
How so?

249
00:13:20,320 --> 00:13:22,610
I met Zhou Hang from Yuanshen Dongfang.

250
00:13:22,750 --> 00:13:24,030
And next Monday,

251
00:13:24,030 --> 00:13:26,690
I'll meet Zhou Hang with Zhang Hongda.

252
00:13:26,710 --> 00:13:27,990
I think

253
00:13:28,910 --> 00:13:31,350
Zhou Hang will be very interested

254
00:13:31,350 --> 00:13:32,720
in Huake Vision.

255
00:13:38,970 --> 00:13:40,040
You're tired?

256
00:13:41,560 --> 00:13:44,230
You seem very obsessed with Huake Vision.

257
00:13:44,230 --> 00:13:45,070
Why?

258
00:13:45,910 --> 00:13:46,480
Yes,

259
00:13:46,480 --> 00:13:47,590
I am very obsessed.

260
00:13:47,590 --> 00:13:48,240
Why?

261
00:13:49,970 --> 00:13:51,050
Because after I graduated,

262
00:13:51,110 --> 00:13:52,790
my first job was at Huake Vision.

263
00:13:53,310 --> 00:13:55,340
After I joined Jade Oak Capital,

264
00:13:55,370 --> 00:13:57,790
the first project I was responsible for was also Huake Vision.

265
00:13:58,220 --> 00:13:59,360
I think

266
00:13:59,510 --> 00:14:00,430
there's no one

267
00:14:00,430 --> 00:14:01,670
who understands Huake Vision better than I do.

268
00:14:03,620 --> 00:14:05,080
I watched Huake Vision

269
00:14:05,080 --> 00:14:08,460
grow from its establishment to where it is today.

270
00:14:10,070 --> 00:14:10,630
Mr. Yu,

271
00:14:11,240 --> 00:14:13,310
I don't know if you believe my judgment.

272
00:14:14,030 --> 00:14:15,310
I think Huake Vision

273
00:14:15,310 --> 00:14:17,510
will definitely become a great company.

274
00:14:18,260 --> 00:14:21,620
So... maybe I feel I have a responsibility

275
00:14:22,190 --> 00:14:23,960
to help it through this difficult time.

276
00:14:24,150 --> 00:14:25,000
It's as simple as that.

277
00:14:25,430 --> 00:14:27,720
If you can persuade Zhou Hang tomorrow,

278
00:14:28,230 --> 00:14:29,110
what reason would I have

279
00:14:29,110 --> 00:14:31,110
to lay off a valuable employee?

280
00:14:32,590 --> 00:14:33,310
Really?

281
00:14:35,030 --> 00:14:35,920
That's a deal then.

282
00:14:36,920 --> 00:14:38,390
Of course, if you can bring in investment

283
00:14:38,390 --> 00:14:39,430
for Huake Vision,

284
00:14:40,700 --> 00:14:42,320
I'll let bygones by bygones.

285
00:14:42,510 --> 00:14:44,150
Your old debts will be gone.

286
00:14:44,510 --> 00:14:44,990
Okay.

287
00:14:45,570 --> 00:14:46,390
I hope you can

288
00:14:46,390 --> 00:14:47,670
be fully committed to your work

289
00:14:47,670 --> 00:14:48,670
from now on.

290
00:14:48,670 --> 00:14:49,230
Okay?

291
00:14:49,230 --> 00:14:49,620
Okay.

292
00:14:49,670 --> 00:14:50,270
Can you do that?

293
00:14:50,270 --> 00:14:50,710
Yes.

294
00:14:50,990 --> 00:14:51,470
Thank you.

295
00:14:51,550 --> 00:14:52,110
Let me help you carry it.

296
00:14:52,110 --> 00:14:52,510
No need.

297
00:14:52,510 --> 00:14:53,230
I can do it.

298
00:14:57,540 --> 00:14:59,340
As your boss, I have one more request.

299
00:14:59,630 --> 00:15:00,550
Okay, Boss. Please go ahead.

300
00:15:02,630 --> 00:15:04,710
Don't let those guys force me to drink too much alcohol later.

301
00:15:08,870 --> 00:15:09,630
Sure.

302
00:15:10,010 --> 00:15:11,290
Absolutely.

303
00:15:23,870 --> 00:15:24,810
We don't have

304
00:15:25,010 --> 00:15:26,920
too much work here compared to

305
00:15:27,550 --> 00:15:28,190
private publishing companies.

306
00:15:28,880 --> 00:15:30,960
This is the main office.

307
00:15:32,740 --> 00:15:33,520
Of course,

308
00:15:34,550 --> 00:15:36,870
the work here is much less compared to your agency.

309
00:15:38,670 --> 00:15:40,950
This was Qiao's office.

310
00:15:41,230 --> 00:15:42,240
He's the former vice president.

311
00:15:42,630 --> 00:15:44,110
He just retired last month.

312
00:15:44,630 --> 00:15:45,630
If you come,

313
00:15:45,690 --> 00:15:46,620
this office

314
00:15:46,620 --> 00:15:47,390
will be yours.

315
00:15:49,280 --> 00:15:50,890
My office is right next door.

316
00:15:51,270 --> 00:15:51,740
Come,

317
00:15:52,340 --> 00:15:53,220
have a seat inside.

318
00:15:57,780 --> 00:15:58,220
Sit.

319
00:15:59,400 --> 00:16:00,670
I'll get you some water.

320
00:16:01,020 --> 00:16:02,060
Don't bother, Mr. Liu.

321
00:16:04,950 --> 00:16:05,870
Our office hours

322
00:16:06,300 --> 00:16:08,650
are from 9 a.m. to 5 p.m.

323
00:16:09,480 --> 00:16:11,160
There aren't any rigid rules.

324
00:16:12,690 --> 00:16:14,670
You just need to make sure the work gets done.

325
00:16:15,390 --> 00:16:16,030
Sit.

326
00:16:18,750 --> 00:16:19,350
We have

327
00:16:20,350 --> 00:16:22,730
public-funded publishing projects every year.

328
00:16:22,840 --> 00:16:23,870
There are also some authors

329
00:16:24,310 --> 00:16:25,110
who write books

330
00:16:25,740 --> 00:16:27,630
on economics and informational topics.

331
00:16:28,470 --> 00:16:30,910
These alone are enough to sustain us.

332
00:16:31,600 --> 00:16:32,590
When you come,

333
00:16:32,630 --> 00:16:33,840
you'll step into Qiao's role,

334
00:16:34,390 --> 00:16:36,710
overseeing self-funded publishing.

335
00:16:37,140 --> 00:16:38,460
It's perfect since you have a wide network,

336
00:16:39,150 --> 00:16:41,570
and you know people in the financial circle.

337
00:16:42,550 --> 00:16:44,360
For those looking to get titles,

338
00:16:44,550 --> 00:16:46,100
attend conferences,

339
00:16:46,190 --> 00:16:47,770
or build their personal brands,

340
00:16:47,870 --> 00:16:49,310
you can introduce them to us.

341
00:16:49,950 --> 00:16:52,170
We can even print as few as 100 copies.

342
00:16:52,670 --> 00:16:53,690
As for the details,

343
00:16:54,110 --> 00:16:54,830
I'll have someone

344
00:16:54,870 --> 00:16:57,230
walk you through them by that time.

345
00:16:58,550 --> 00:16:59,270
Okay.

346
00:16:59,510 --> 00:17:00,550
Don't feel pressured.

347
00:17:01,310 --> 00:17:02,750
We don't do things like

348
00:17:02,780 --> 00:17:04,030
performance evaluations here.

349
00:17:04,030 --> 00:17:04,910
If there's work, we do it.

350
00:17:05,589 --> 00:17:08,190
If not, we collaborate with institutions,

351
00:17:08,550 --> 00:17:10,280
choose topics,

352
00:17:10,480 --> 00:17:13,510
or explore cooperative publishing.

353
00:17:14,140 --> 00:17:14,859
So,

354
00:17:15,349 --> 00:17:17,069
please don't feel pressured.

355
00:17:18,060 --> 00:17:18,710
Okay.

356
00:17:20,319 --> 00:17:20,990
Well then,

357
00:17:22,020 --> 00:17:24,710
when do you plan to start working here?

358
00:17:25,950 --> 00:17:27,829
The salary and benefits are already settled.

359
00:17:27,829 --> 00:17:30,250
Mr. Liu said as long as the group agrees to let me go,

360
00:17:30,310 --> 00:17:32,070
I can start anytime.

361
00:17:32,790 --> 00:17:33,710
What do you think?

362
00:17:34,310 --> 00:17:35,030
It's quite good.

363
00:17:35,280 --> 00:17:36,290
Suitable for those in retirement.

364
00:17:38,040 --> 00:17:40,380
It's actually just a different way of living,

365
00:17:40,590 --> 00:17:42,270
a slower-paced lifestyle.

366
00:17:42,550 --> 00:17:43,030
Right?

367
00:17:44,310 --> 00:17:44,900
Zhou Hang,

368
00:17:44,900 --> 00:17:46,820
this isn't about pace, you know?

369
00:17:47,070 --> 00:17:48,470
It's about the lack of challenge.

370
00:17:50,030 --> 00:17:51,310
I think it's great.

371
00:17:51,950 --> 00:17:53,510
With more free time,

372
00:17:53,630 --> 00:17:55,710
you can do things you want to do.

373
00:17:56,480 --> 00:17:57,990
I remember you told me before

374
00:17:57,990 --> 00:17:58,850
a university

375
00:17:58,990 --> 00:18:01,190
offered you a guest professorship.

376
00:18:01,740 --> 00:18:03,350
When you're free, you can

377
00:18:04,110 --> 00:18:05,720
give lessons and train some new talents for them.

378
00:18:05,720 --> 00:18:06,390
Isn't that great?

379
00:18:07,380 --> 00:18:08,190
Zhou Hang,

380
00:18:08,190 --> 00:18:09,680
why do I feel like

381
00:18:09,680 --> 00:18:11,880
you're trying to persuade me to go?

382
00:18:12,230 --> 00:18:13,350
Is it that obvious?

383
00:18:13,380 --> 00:18:15,030
It's quite obvious, okay?

384
00:18:16,150 --> 00:18:18,340
Actually, we both are too busy.

385
00:18:18,990 --> 00:18:20,150
You're busy, and I'm busy too.

386
00:18:21,070 --> 00:18:23,010
When we have children,

387
00:18:23,140 --> 00:18:24,910
they'll need someone to accompany them, right?

388
00:18:25,670 --> 00:18:27,660
So I want you to seriously think about it.

389
00:18:28,430 --> 00:18:28,830
Okay.

390
00:18:28,830 --> 00:18:29,430
I got it.

391
00:18:29,950 --> 00:18:31,110
Let me think about it, okay?

392
00:18:31,780 --> 00:18:32,390
What?

393
00:18:32,590 --> 00:18:33,540
My dear wife,

394
00:18:34,270 --> 00:18:35,830
are you worried I can't support you?

395
00:18:36,100 --> 00:18:36,710
Zhou Hang,

396
00:18:36,710 --> 00:18:37,910
what's wrong with you today?

397
00:18:38,590 --> 00:18:40,470
You're speaking so sweetly.

398
00:18:41,110 --> 00:18:42,150
You've got goose bumps?

399
00:18:44,790 --> 00:18:45,270
Alright,

400
00:18:46,190 --> 00:18:47,070
let's talk when we get home.

401
00:18:47,070 --> 00:18:47,800
Bye bye.

402
00:18:48,590 --> 00:18:49,110
Come in.

403
00:18:52,870 --> 00:18:53,630
Well, Mr. Zhou,

404
00:18:53,710 --> 00:18:55,030
I've got an update on Jade Oak Capital.

405
00:18:55,030 --> 00:18:55,990
They plan to withdraw the lawsuit.

406
00:18:56,590 --> 00:18:57,270
Great.

407
00:18:57,880 --> 00:18:59,310
What's the situation on Wu Yueting's side?

408
00:19:00,590 --> 00:19:01,630
I heard that Coroman

409
00:19:01,630 --> 00:19:04,070
is currently stuck at animal testing and model validation.

410
00:19:04,310 --> 00:19:06,390
The third-party testing seems to be fine this time,

411
00:19:06,390 --> 00:19:08,110
but the process will still take some time.

412
00:19:08,110 --> 00:19:09,030
Third-party?

413
00:19:09,650 --> 00:19:10,840
Which testing agency is it?

414
00:19:11,190 --> 00:19:11,710
Huiyao.

415
00:19:12,140 --> 00:19:12,930
Huiyao?

416
00:19:13,840 --> 00:19:14,280
Mr. Fang.

417
00:19:14,310 --> 00:19:14,750
Yes.

418
00:19:16,750 --> 00:19:17,660
Help me make an appointment with him.

419
00:19:17,660 --> 00:19:18,750
I want to play golf with him this weekend.

420
00:19:19,950 --> 00:19:21,270
Figure out a way

421
00:19:21,500 --> 00:19:23,830
to make Coroman know about our appointment.

422
00:19:24,020 --> 00:19:24,550
Got it.

423
00:19:25,070 --> 00:19:25,650
You can leave now.

424
00:20:24,550 --> 00:20:25,600
Chief Editor Xie.

425
00:20:27,810 --> 00:20:28,570
What a coincidence.

426
00:20:28,590 --> 00:20:29,760
Mr. Wang.

427
00:20:30,280 --> 00:20:31,780
I didn't expect to run into you here.

428
00:20:31,810 --> 00:20:32,670
Yeah.

429
00:20:32,750 --> 00:20:34,110
You're here...

430
00:20:34,160 --> 00:20:34,870
No.

431
00:20:35,180 --> 00:20:38,340
Now I work at a private publishing company,

432
00:20:38,850 --> 00:20:40,030
primarily publishing

433
00:20:40,110 --> 00:20:41,030
and distributing

434
00:20:41,210 --> 00:20:43,560
popular books on finance and economics.

435
00:20:43,590 --> 00:20:45,030
I specially came here today

436
00:20:45,130 --> 00:20:46,980
to assess the market situation.

437
00:20:47,020 --> 00:20:48,600
Actually, these private publishers

438
00:20:48,670 --> 00:20:49,680
are doing quite well.

439
00:20:49,740 --> 00:20:51,180
Yes, they're full of energy

440
00:20:51,220 --> 00:20:52,040
and ambition.

441
00:20:52,060 --> 00:20:52,940
Yes, indeed.

442
00:20:53,950 --> 00:20:55,920
You look in good shape.

443
00:20:56,230 --> 00:20:57,000
Really?

444
00:20:59,190 --> 00:21:00,310
You... You are...

445
00:21:00,310 --> 00:21:01,070
free today?

446
00:21:01,090 --> 00:21:02,040
Yes, I'm not too busy at the moment.

447
00:21:02,070 --> 00:21:03,150
I just came here to look around

448
00:21:03,150 --> 00:21:04,710
and see what new books there are.

449
00:21:05,190 --> 00:21:06,070
Do you have time?

450
00:21:06,910 --> 00:21:07,870
Can I... Can I

451
00:21:08,270 --> 00:21:09,990
invite you for a cup of coffee?

452
00:21:11,790 --> 00:21:12,350
Thank you.

453
00:21:25,110 --> 00:21:25,990
Mr. Wang,

454
00:21:26,950 --> 00:21:29,340
do you want to talk to me about something?

455
00:21:31,830 --> 00:21:33,340
I heard about what happened to you.

456
00:21:34,770 --> 00:21:38,160
I... I'm not here to gloat.

457
00:21:38,640 --> 00:21:39,470
Mr. Wang,

458
00:21:40,030 --> 00:21:41,750
why would I think like that about you?

459
00:21:42,710 --> 00:21:43,480
Actually,

460
00:21:44,140 --> 00:21:46,090
I do feel a bit regretful.

461
00:21:47,590 --> 00:21:49,370
When I resigned,

462
00:21:50,070 --> 00:21:52,070
I was very angry

463
00:21:53,310 --> 00:21:54,160
at the group

464
00:21:55,020 --> 00:21:56,070
and even at you.

465
00:21:56,380 --> 00:21:58,950
I really didn't understand the grading thing

466
00:21:59,230 --> 00:22:00,550
you did.

467
00:22:02,700 --> 00:22:04,500
Later,

468
00:22:04,750 --> 00:22:06,310
I thought about it.

469
00:22:06,390 --> 00:22:08,510
I calmed down.

470
00:22:08,830 --> 00:22:10,110
And I realized

471
00:22:10,550 --> 00:22:11,710
many things

472
00:22:13,390 --> 00:22:14,950
are beyond our control.

473
00:22:15,670 --> 00:22:17,160
Everyone has their moments when they have no choice.

474
00:22:17,750 --> 00:22:20,050
It was not your fault or mine.

475
00:22:20,310 --> 00:22:22,150
Perhaps, our industry has really entered

476
00:22:22,990 --> 00:22:24,950
a new era.

477
00:22:26,310 --> 00:22:27,260
Mr. Wang,

478
00:22:27,830 --> 00:22:29,430
thank you for your understanding.

479
00:22:29,670 --> 00:22:30,670
Don't thank me.

480
00:22:31,270 --> 00:22:32,870
I should thank you.

481
00:22:33,480 --> 00:22:34,930
For what?

482
00:22:36,130 --> 00:22:38,220
I heard that you

483
00:22:38,670 --> 00:22:40,390
recommended me to Mr. Xu.

484
00:22:40,710 --> 00:22:42,390
That's why I'm at this company.

485
00:22:43,300 --> 00:22:44,970
Mr. Xu didn't tell me this.

486
00:22:45,070 --> 00:22:46,640
I found out through the HR department.

487
00:22:46,710 --> 00:22:48,270
They casually mentioned

488
00:22:48,270 --> 00:22:50,680
that I was referred internally.

489
00:22:51,560 --> 00:22:52,540
I guessed

490
00:22:52,870 --> 00:22:54,170
it must have been you.

491
00:22:54,350 --> 00:22:56,110
Otherwise, how could an old man like me

492
00:22:56,230 --> 00:22:58,790
compete with those fresh graduates?

493
00:23:00,090 --> 00:23:02,290
These two cups of coffee don't count.

494
00:23:02,510 --> 00:23:04,310
If... If there's a chance, I...

495
00:23:04,310 --> 00:23:06,100
How do they say it in the north?

496
00:23:06,270 --> 00:23:07,590
I'll treat you to a meal.

497
00:23:09,310 --> 00:23:10,790
Can I order the dishes?

498
00:23:10,790 --> 00:23:11,670
Of course.

499
00:23:12,110 --> 00:23:12,830
Mr. Wang,

500
00:23:13,310 --> 00:23:14,570
actually, it was

501
00:23:14,870 --> 00:23:15,990
not like that.

502
00:23:16,710 --> 00:23:18,390
I would never

503
00:23:18,710 --> 00:23:20,010
recommend someone

504
00:23:20,390 --> 00:23:22,940
out of sympathy.

505
00:23:23,190 --> 00:23:26,150
I recommended you simply because you're an experienced editor

506
00:23:26,150 --> 00:23:28,100
with a strong sense of responsibility.

507
00:23:28,270 --> 00:23:29,430
This kind of person

508
00:23:29,430 --> 00:23:30,670
is invaluable to Mr. Xu.

509
00:23:30,950 --> 00:23:32,230
I just let him know

510
00:23:32,230 --> 00:23:33,790
he had the opportunity

511
00:23:34,320 --> 00:23:36,550
to bring someone like you on board.

512
00:23:36,630 --> 00:23:37,270
That's all.

513
00:23:37,430 --> 00:23:39,250
I didn't do anything else.

514
00:23:41,360 --> 00:23:42,890
If you put it that way,

515
00:23:43,670 --> 00:23:44,960
I feel even more guilty.

516
00:23:45,790 --> 00:23:48,700
Actually, when I left China Business Wave,

517
00:23:49,550 --> 00:23:51,070
there was one task I didn't complete properly.

518
00:23:51,070 --> 00:23:53,110
I've felt guilty about it ever since.

519
00:23:53,710 --> 00:23:54,870
Mr. Wang, about this matter...

520
00:23:54,870 --> 00:23:56,920
If I had insisted a bit more,

521
00:23:57,140 --> 00:23:59,270
you wouldn't have encountered so many problems.

522
00:24:00,630 --> 00:24:01,710
What do you mean?

523
00:24:05,710 --> 00:24:07,270
You know about Xu Delin's article,

524
00:24:07,670 --> 00:24:08,510
right?

525
00:24:08,820 --> 00:24:09,670
Of course.

526
00:24:10,300 --> 00:24:12,630
I already found something wrong

527
00:24:12,630 --> 00:24:14,190
before it went to print.

528
00:24:15,920 --> 00:24:18,170
The data and the initial

529
00:24:18,270 --> 00:24:20,880
and secondary reviews were completely inconsistent.

530
00:24:21,070 --> 00:24:22,910
Then why didn't you say anything at that time?

531
00:24:22,950 --> 00:24:24,030
I did.

532
00:24:24,470 --> 00:24:25,710
I raised the issue.

533
00:24:26,700 --> 00:24:27,750
I went to Lv Jian

534
00:24:27,750 --> 00:24:29,590
and mentioned it to him in person.

535
00:24:29,590 --> 00:24:30,430
He didn't...

536
00:24:31,400 --> 00:24:32,990
He didn't believe me.

537
00:24:32,990 --> 00:24:33,790
He even said

538
00:24:34,190 --> 00:24:36,910
I was doing that just to earn praise.

539
00:24:36,910 --> 00:24:37,470
Can you believe it?

540
00:24:39,030 --> 00:24:40,070
Forget it.

541
00:24:42,430 --> 00:24:43,990
I've been thinking about it recently.

542
00:24:44,310 --> 00:24:47,770
I don't think he didn't believe me.

543
00:24:47,990 --> 00:24:49,750
He knew exactly what I was trying to say.

544
00:24:54,380 --> 00:24:55,650
Xu Delin

545
00:24:57,410 --> 00:24:59,700
is very close to Lv Jian.

546
00:25:00,960 --> 00:25:02,270
I saw them

547
00:25:02,270 --> 00:25:03,950
together alone a few times,

548
00:25:04,230 --> 00:25:05,870
discussing something.

549
00:25:06,250 --> 00:25:07,670
I thought what if something happened.

550
00:25:09,160 --> 00:25:11,080
There aren't so many ifs.

551
00:25:13,080 --> 00:25:16,040
I'm not someone who likes to meddle,

552
00:25:16,950 --> 00:25:17,670
but

553
00:25:17,690 --> 00:25:20,760
after the incident involving the article about Jade Oak Capital,

554
00:25:22,010 --> 00:25:23,190
I found

555
00:25:24,000 --> 00:25:25,670
there's something wrong with him.

556
00:25:27,120 --> 00:25:30,850
Later, Xu Delin resigned and joined Coroman.

557
00:25:30,900 --> 00:25:32,070
Wu Yueting's company?

558
00:25:33,810 --> 00:25:35,460
It's very obvious.

559
00:25:37,530 --> 00:25:39,330
I'm not trying to drive a wedge.

560
00:25:39,870 --> 00:25:41,890
I was worried I might be in trouble.

561
00:25:42,830 --> 00:25:44,190
You should

562
00:25:45,710 --> 00:25:47,230
know the truth.

563
00:25:48,980 --> 00:25:49,870
I don't think

564
00:25:50,670 --> 00:25:52,790
it was just an accident.

565
00:26:10,390 --> 00:26:11,150
It's me.

566
00:26:11,370 --> 00:26:12,150
Linhui.

567
00:26:12,230 --> 00:26:12,790
I want to know

568
00:26:12,790 --> 00:26:14,350
what the group plans to do next.

569
00:26:14,830 --> 00:26:16,190
I'll go check what the group

570
00:26:16,190 --> 00:26:17,310
plans to do next.

571
00:26:22,990 --> 00:26:23,870
Hello?

572
00:26:26,310 --> 00:26:27,430
Chief Editor Xie?

573
00:26:28,070 --> 00:26:29,030
She's not here right now.

574
00:26:29,050 --> 00:26:30,410
What's the matter?

575
00:26:36,590 --> 00:26:37,190
Hello.

576
00:26:38,390 --> 00:26:39,310
I'm Lv Jian.

577
00:26:40,620 --> 00:26:42,080
I'm in charge here now.

578
00:26:42,670 --> 00:26:43,710
What can I do for you?

579
00:26:45,710 --> 00:26:46,190
Okay.

580
00:26:47,550 --> 00:26:48,230
How about this?

581
00:26:48,530 --> 00:26:50,370
Send me the files first,

582
00:26:50,380 --> 00:26:52,270
or email them to me so I can take a look.

583
00:26:52,460 --> 00:26:53,100
-Okay?
-Chief Editor Lv.

584
00:26:53,100 --> 00:26:54,910
This is the payment for the author.

